HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 741
By Lamberth
A RESOLUTION to provide for a recess in the proceedings of the
2026 regular session of the One Hundred
Fourteenth General Assembly in observance of
Martin Luther King Jr. Day.
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that the 2026 regular session of the One Hundred Fourteenth General
Assembly stand in recess at the close of business in both houses on Thursday, January 15,
2026, and reconvene on Wednesday, January 21, 2026, at 8:30 a.m. (CST).
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that pursuant to Article II, Section 16, of the Constitution
of Tennessee, the Senate, by its concurrence in this resolution, consents to this recess.
